snippet: An explosion at a mosque and attacks on several polling places show how far the country has to go.
abstract: International monitors praise Libya’s first election in decades as a surprisingly successful expression of the public will; early results indicate broad success for a coalition of parties led by Mahmoud Jibril; all sides appear to accept the overall pattern of the results, and there are no major allegations of electoral fraud.
lead_paragraph: An explosion at a mosque and attacks on several polling places show how far the country has to go.

headline.seo: Attacks in Libya Show Unrest Despite Fairly Smooth Election
headline.main: Despite Fairly Smooth Election, Attacks in Libya Show Unrest
